.TH SCHUPFN 1 "2026-04-22" "schupfn 0.1.0"
.SH NAME
schupfn \- run toolbox containers in virtual machines
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B schupfn enter
.RI [ name ]
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B schupfn list
.br
.B schupfn clean
.RI [ name ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B schupfn
boots a toolbox container as a virtual machine using
.BR virtme\-ng (1).
The current working directory is mounted read\-write inside the VM at
the same path; everything else on the host is inaccessible.
.PP
The intended use is sandboxing: the VM boundary provides stronger
isolation than a container, which matters when running untrusted code
or AI agents that might try to break out of their sandbox.
.PP
The workflow is:
.IP 1. 4
Create and configure a toolbox container the usual way
.RI ( "toolbox create" ,
.IR "toolbox run" ).
.IP 2.
Run
.B schupfn enter
to export the container's filesystem, boot it as a VM with the host
kernel, and SSH in.
.IP 3.
Work inside the VM as you would inside
.BR toolbox (1).
When you exit, the VM shuts down.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS enter \fR[\fIname\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
Export the toolbox container
.I name
to a local rootfs and boot it as a VM.
If
.I name
is omitted, the
.B container
field from the configuration file is used (see
.BR "CONFIGURATION FILE" ).
.PP
The container must have these packages installed:
.BR openssh\-server ,
.BR systemd\-udev ,
.BR busybox .
If any are missing,
.B schupfn
will offer to install them.
.PP
The options are as follows:
.TP
.BI \-\-export\-ro " path"
Make an additional host path available in the VM.
If
.I path
is a directory (or a symlink to one), it is mounted read\-only at
its original absolute path.
If
.I path
is a file (or a symlink to one), it is copied into the VM at its
original absolute path (directory structure is preserved).
This option may be given multiple times.
.TP
.BI \-\-export\-rw " path"
Like
.B \-\-export\-ro
but directories are mounted read\-write.
This option may be given multiple times.
.TP
.BI \-\-command " cmd"
Run
.I cmd
in the VM instead of starting an interactive shell.
The exit code of
.I cmd
is propagated as the exit code of
.BR schupfn .
.TP
.BI \-\-config " path"
Load the configuration file from
.I path
instead of searching for
.B .schupfn/config.yml
in parent directories.
It is an error if the file does not exist.
.TP
.B \-\-refresh
Force re\-export of the rootfs, even if the cached copy appears fresh.
.TP
.B \-\-deep\-check
Use
.B podman diff
for more thorough staleness detection when deciding whether to
re\-export.
.TP
.BI \-\-memory " size"
Amount of memory for the VM, e.g.\&
.BR 4G ,
.BR 512M .
The default is
.BR 4G .
.TP
.BI \-\-cpus " n"
Number of CPUs for the VM.
Defaults to the host CPU count.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-network
Disable the extra user\-mode network device.
The internal SSH network device is unaffected.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Show VM boot output on stderr.
.SS list
Show cached rootfs entries with their freshness status, size, and
export date.
Freshness is one of:
.TP
.B fresh
The cached rootfs matches the current container state.
.TP
.B stale
The container has changed since the rootfs was exported.
.TP
.B orphaned
The container no longer exists.
.SS clean \fR[\fIname\fR]
Remove cached rootfs entries.
If
.I name
is given, only that entry is removed.
Otherwise all entries are removed after confirmation.
.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
.B schupfn
searches from
.B $PWD
upward for a file named
.BR .schupfn/config.yml .
The first one found is loaded.
If no local config file is found,
.B schupfn
falls back to
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/schupfn/ :
first
.IR <container>\-config.yml
(if the container name is known from the command line), then
.IR default\-config.yml .
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
defaults to
.IR ~/.config
if unset.
.PP
Requires
.BR yq (1)
to be installed; if no configuration file is found,
.B yq
is not needed.
.PP
CLI arguments always take precedence over configuration file values.
For
.B \-\-export\-ro
and
.BR \-\-export\-rw ,
the configuration file list and CLI list are merged (config entries
first).
.PP
The following keys are recognised:
.TP
.B container
.RI ( string )
Default container name, used when none is given on the command line.
.TP
.B command
.RI ( string )
Command to run in the VM instead of an interactive shell.
Same as
.BR \-\-command .
.TP
.B export\-ro
.RI ( "list of paths" )
Paths to export read\-only into the VM.
Same as
.BR \-\-export\-ro .
.TP
.B export\-rw
.RI ( "list of paths" )
Paths to export read\-write into the VM.
Same as
.BR \-\-export\-rw .
.TP
.B vm.memory
.RI ( string )
VM memory.
Same as
.BR \-\-memory .
.TP
.B vm.cpus
.RI ( int )
VM CPU count.
Same as
.BR \-\-cpus .
.TP
.B vm.network
.RI ( bool )
Set to
.B false
to disable the extra network device.
Same as
.BR \-\-no\-network .
.TP
.B ssh_key
.RI ( path )
SSH private key to use when connecting to the VM.
The path is validated at startup; a missing file is a fatal error.
.SS Example
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
container: my\-toolbox
command: make test

export\-ro:
  \- ~/src/shared\-lib
  \- ~/.zshrc

export\-rw:
  \- ~/src/work\-in\-progress

vm:
  memory: 8G
  cpus: 4
  network: false

ssh_key: ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
.EE
.in
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for user\-level configuration files.
Defaults to
.IR ~/.config .
When no local
.I .schupfn/config.yml
is found,
.B schupfn
looks for
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/schupfn/<container>\-config.yml ,
then
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/schupfn/default\-config.yml .
.TP
.B XDG_CACHE_HOME
Base directory for cached rootfs trees.
Defaults to
.IR ~/.cache .
The cache lives under
.IR $XDG_CACHE_HOME/schupfn/roots/ .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .schupfn/config.yml
Per\-project configuration file, searched from
.B $PWD
upward.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/schupfn/<container>\-config.yml
Container\-specific user\-level configuration file, used when no local
.I .schupfn/config.yml
is found and the container name is known from the command line.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/schupfn/default\-config.yml
User\-level default configuration file, used when no local
.I .schupfn/config.yml
or container\-specific config is found.
Defaults to
.IR ~/.config/schupfn/default\-config.yml .
.TP
.I ~/.cache/schupfn/roots/<name>/
Cached rootfs for a container.
Managed by
.B schupfn list
and
.BR "schupfn clean" .
.SH EXIT STATUS
In interactive mode (no
.BR \-\-command ),
.B schupfn
exits 0 on success.
Non\-zero SSH exit codes produce a warning but
.B schupfn
still exits 0.
.PP
With
.BR \-\-command ,
the exit code of the remote command is forwarded as the exit code of
.BR schupfn .
.SH EXAMPLES
Enter a toolbox as a VM:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn enter mybox
.EE
.in
.PP
Mount extra directories and copy dotfiles:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn enter mybox \-\-export\-ro ~/src/lib \-\-export\-ro ~/.vimrc
.EE
.in
.PP
Run a single command and exit:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn enter mybox \-\-command "make -j$(nproc) test"
.EE
.in
.PP
Use a config file so you only need to type:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn enter
.EE
.in
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR toolbox (1),
.BR podman (1),
.BR vng (1),
.BR ssh (1),
.BR yq (1)
